"867-5309/Jenny"

Misheard Lyrics:

Jenny, I'm not a robot

Original Lyrics:

Jenny, I got your number

"867-5309/Jenny"

Misheard Lyrics:

Jenny, I’m not your mother

or

Jenny, I’m not your father

Original Lyrics:

Jenny, I got your number

"867-5309/Jenny"

Misheard Lyrics:

Jenny, I got your rumbler

Original Lyrics:

Jenny, I got your number

"867-5309/Jenny"

Misheard Lyrics:

Jenny, I got your mother

Original Lyrics:

Jenny, I got your number

"867-5309 (Jenny)"

Misheard Lyrics:

Benny, I got your number, I need to make you mine.

Benny, don't change your number,

Original Lyrics:

Jenny, I got your number, I need to make you mine.

Jenny, don't change your number,

Story about this misheard lyric by: likalaruku

Another friend thought it was Danny. Either way, we thought the song was one big gay joke.

"867-5309 (Jenny)"

The Funny Lyrics:

I got it (I got it)

I got your number on the wall

I got it (I got it)

For a good time, for a good time call!

Why They're Funny:

The whole song, as far as I gather, is about how he saw a message on a restroom wall saying 'For a good time call Jenny at 867-5309' and decided to make her his girlfriend. I needn't explain any further why that's funny.

Submitted by: Princess Ana

"867-5309 (Jenny)"

The Nonsensical Lyrics:

Jenny, Jenny, You're the girl for me.

You don't know me, but you make so happy.

Why They're Nonsensical:

Since Jenny doesn't know the narrator (and vice versa), then how does he know what she's thinking about him? How can she compare him with other losers if the two have never met?

Submitted by: Khalil
